<section xmlns="http://xml.house.gov/schemas/uslm/1.0" style="-uslm-lc:I80" id="id522d6295-3a70-11f1-9e0c-dcbb1364dae6" identifier="/us/usc/t28/s110"><num value="110">§ 110.</num><heading> New Jersey</heading><content>
<p style="-uslm-lc:I11" class="indent0">New Jersey constitutes one judicial district.</p>
<p style="-uslm-lc:I56" class="indent4 firstIndent-2">Court shall be held at Camden, Newark and Trenton.</p>
</content><sourceCredit id="id522d6296-3a70-11f1-9e0c-dcbb1364dae6">(<ref href="/us/act/1948-06-25/ch646">June 25, 1948, ch. 646</ref>, <ref href="/us/stat/62/885">62 Stat. 885</ref>.)</sourceCredit>
<notes type="uscNote" id="id522d6297-3a70-11f1-9e0c-dcbb1364dae6">
<note style="-uslm-lc:I74" topic="historicalAndRevision" id="id522d6298-3a70-11f1-9e0c-dcbb1364dae6"><heading class="centered smallCaps">Historical and Revision Notes</heading><p style="-uslm-lc:I21" class="indent0">Based on title 28, U.S.C., 1940 ed., § 176 (<ref href="/us/act/1911-03-03/ch231/s96">Mar. 3, 1911, ch. 231, § 96</ref>, <ref href="/us/stat/36/1119">36 Stat. 1119</ref>; <ref href="/us/act/1912-08-09/ch277">Aug. 9, 1912, ch. 277</ref>, <ref href="/us/stat/37/265">37 Stat. 265</ref>; <ref href="/us/act/1913-02-14/ch53">Feb. 14, 1913, ch. 53</ref>, <ref href="/us/stat/37/674">37 Stat. 674</ref>; <ref href="/us/act/1926-05-17/ch311">May 17, 1926, ch. 311</ref>, <ref href="/us/stat/44/561">44 Stat. 561</ref>).</p>
<p style="-uslm-lc:I21" class="indent0">Provisions relating to maintenance of offices by the clerk and marshal were omitted as covered by sections 452, 541 [see 561], 542 [see 561], and 751 of this title.</p>
<p style="-uslm-lc:I21" class="indent0">Changes in arrangement and phraseology were made.</p>
</note>
